SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 953
By Hatcher
A RESOLUTION to commend Lillian Rose for exemplary service
as a legislative intern.
WHEREAS, each legislative session, the members of this General Assembly are
pleased to recognize certain persons who have committed themselves, through their adroit
service, to the betterment of the legislative process; and
WHEREAS, Lillian Rose is one such individual, who has distinguished herself in her role
as a legislative intern for Senator Tom Hatcher; her work has resulted in innumerable benefits
for the legislators she assisted and the General Assembly as a whole; and
WHEREAS, a student of the Tennessee State University (TSU) Honors College, where
she is highly regarded by her peers, Ms. Rose has achieved academic success while pursuing a
degree in political science with a minor in English; and
WHEREAS, during her collegiate career, Lillian Rose has served the Sigma Tau Delta
honor society as secretary, Alpha Lambda Delta as a charter member, and the Academic
Achievement and Retention Center as an English and political science tutor; additionally, she
has been the lead event planner and communication facilitator for TSU's political science
program since 2023; and
WHEREAS, a member of Phi Alpha Delta Law Fraternity, International, Ms. Rose
participated in the Tennessee Intercollegiate State Legislature's Appellate Moot Court Collegiate
Challenge, where she served as a co-captain in 2025 and was named Rookie of the Year and
Best Respondent Lawyer in 2024; and
WHEREAS, Lillian Rose is a leader in her community and has served the YMCA of
Memphis and the Mid-South as a youth counselor, in which role she helped children advance
their skills in English and spelling; and
SJR0953
015603
- 1 -

WHEREAS, she has also devoted her time and talents to the Trevecca Nazarene
Rehabilitation and Healing Center, the Jefferson Street Community Cleanup, the Monroe Carell
Jr. Children's Hospital at Vanderbilt, the Southern Festival of Books, and the National Breast
Cancer Foundation, among several other worthy endeavors; and
WHEREAS, eager to familiarize herself with the characteristics and complexities of
Tennessee State government and to further her studies, Lillian Rose brought her many abilities
and singular expertise to Capitol Hill for the 2026 session of the One Hundred Fourteenth
General Assembly; and
WHEREAS, throughout the 2026 legislative session, Ms. Rose has surpassed all criteria
that define a devoted and conscientious legislative intern; and
WHEREAS, Lillian Rose has performed her many duties with extraordinary insight and
rare decorum; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we recognize and honor Lillian Rose for her
outstanding service as a legislative intern for Senator Tom Hatcher and extend to her our best
wishes for every future success.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
